                                <div class="table-responsive">
                                    <strong>No Dues Certificate</strong>
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <p>Facility to certify outstanding/No Dues has been added to ESS portal, where HR user can initiate No Dues approval process for concerned employee, and all stakeholders will be able to post outstanding/No Dues.</p>
                                    <p>Go to No Dues -> No Dues Master for Generate Employee No Dues.</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/1.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>Here, HR user will Enter employee SAP id and press search button. Employee basic details will be displayed:</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/2.jpg" />
                                    <p>Enter Resign Date and Relieve Date and mode of leaving and click Submit button.</p>
                                    <p>This will initiate the No Dues process and the Department head of leaving employee will be able to process further before 4 days of Relieve date. An auto-mail will be sent to department head accordingly.</p>
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>Go to -> No Dues Section Head / Hod ->No Dues Entry</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/3.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>No dues (department of leaving employee) creator user can enter details here. List of all employees leaving will be shown. Click on the plus sign button to open popup window for entry:</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/4.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>Enter all details: particular, remarks and amount and click on plus button to add details.</p>
                                    <p>Click on Submit Button to Save details.</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/5.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>Reopening same record after saving will show remove button to remove the record if required:</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/6.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>Go to -> Section Head / HOD ->Approve No Dues.</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/7.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>List of pending no dues for release (by respective HOD) are shown in table:</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/8.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>Click on information button to open popup window to view details:</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/9.jpg" />
                                    <p>Click on Green approve button to release the No dues entry.</p>
                                    <p>No Dues entry for all other departments will be available only after release from Department Head of leaving employee. Hence maintaining time schedule is vital. An auto-mail will be sent to all corresponding department users/HODs.</p>
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>GSS Departments No Dues Entry:</p>
                                    <p>For Creator:</p>
                                    <p>Go to -> No Dues Details </p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/10.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>List of pending No Dues Records are displayed to all concerned who records the no dues for the department:</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/11.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>Click on plus button to open popup for details entry:</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/12.jpg" />
                                    <p>After entering details (Particulars, Remarks and Amount) click on plus button to add details in grid. Multiple details can be added.</p>
                                    <p>In case of wrong entry, click on delete button to remove entry. And click on submit button to save details.</p>
                                    <p>The below message display after successfully saves your details.</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/13.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>No Dues Entry users can also edit details after saving, before the same is released by his department no dues releaser. After release by HOD, data cannot be changed.</p>
                                    <p>Click on edit button to open window with saved data:</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/14.jpg" /><br /><br />
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/15.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>For No Dues Entry of HR Department:</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/16.jpg" /><br /><br />
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/17.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>No Dues Release by GSS Department releaser:</p>
                                    <p>Go to -> No Dues Release.</p>
                                    <img class="img-thumbnail" src="~/UserManuals/images/NoDues/18.jpg" />
                                    <hr />
                                    <p>List of records pending for release are displayed:</p>
